<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Ugo Giordano"
>
	<p>
		I'm Ugo Giordano, a Senior Software Engineer at Red Hat on the OpenShift AI
		platform team, where I contribute to the Kubernetes operators that power the
		platform and focus on hardening its security posture. I work across 20+
		repositories, building Go libraries, admission webhooks, and CI/CD automation.
		Recent work includes remediating a platform-wide RBAC misconfiguration across
		22 operators and automating security assessments across 135+ repositories
		using AI-powered analysis.
	</p>
	<p>
		I hold a Ph.D. in Software Reliability Engineering from the University of
		Naples Federico II, where I researched SDN control plane reliability. During
		that work I contributed to Nokia Bell Labs' NetUnix project and co-authored
		papers on SDN control plane performance testing and static analysis
		prioritization.
	</p>
	<p>
		At Red Hat I work across the Kubernetes and AI/ML stack. I'm a Red Hat
		Certified Architect (RHCA), Certified Engineer (RHCE), and hold eight
		Red Hat certifications in total. My day-to-day involves Go, Python,
		TypeScript and the cloud-native toolchain. Beyond security, I spend a lot
		of time building tools that make engineering workflows faster and less
		manual. I'm particularly interested in how AI integrates into real developer
		tooling, not as a chatbot but as an agent that can actually do things.
	</p>
	<p>
		Before the PhD I competed in the International Olympiad in Informatics. These
		days I care about security, reliability, testing and building things that
		actually work in production.
	</p>
	<p>
		Find me on <a href="https://github.com/ugiordan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> and
		<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ugogiordano" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>,
		or <a href="/cv.pdf">download my CV</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
